# CourseNotif Context (Current Snapshot)

Last updated: March 11, 2026

## 1) Project identity

- Project name: CourseNotif
- Current stage: Implemented MVP (active development)
- Architecture: Node.js app with Express API/UI + worker + PostgreSQL
- Primary goal: Monitor tracked courses and notify users when seats open (`os > 0`)

## 2) What is currently implemented

1. Data model and persistence
- PostgreSQL schema exists in `db/schema.sql`
- Core tables: `users`, `courses`, `user_courses`, `shared_latest_jsp_file`, `shared_vsb_session`, `notification_attempts`, `auth_otp_challenges`, `auth_sessions`
- `user_courses` supports:
  - `display_name`
  - `tracking_status` (`active` | `notified` | `invalid`)
  - `notified_at`
  - `invalid_attempts`
  - `invalid_notified_at`
  - `updated_at`
- DB layer exists in `src/db.js` with compatibility migration guard (`ensureCompatibility`)
- Resume/retry support is implemented in DB helpers:
  - `markUserCourseNotified`
  - `markUserCourseInvalid`
  - `resumeUserCourseForUser`
  - `resetNotificationStateForUserCourse`

2. API server
- Express server in `src/apiServer.js`
- Implemented endpoints:
  - `GET /api/health`
  - `GET /api/metrics` (optional bearer auth)
  - `GET /api/worker-health` (optional bearer auth)
  - `GET /api/auth/me`
  - `POST /api/auth/send-otp`
  - `POST /api/auth/verify-otp`
  - `POST /api/auth/logout`
  - `GET /api/tracked-courses` (auth required)
  - `POST /api/tracked-courses` (auth required)
  - `POST /api/tracked-courses/:id/resume` (auth required)
  - `DELETE /api/tracked-courses/:id` (auth required)
- `POST /api/tracked-courses` auto-resumes rows currently in `notified`/`invalid` state
- Tracked-course responses include status fields (`trackingStatus`, `notifiedAt`, `invalidAttempts`, `invalidNotifiedAt`)
- Serves `index.html` at `GET /`

3. Frontend
- Single-page UI in `index.html`
- Supports:
  - passwordless email OTP sign-in
  - resend OTP with cooldown
  - logout
  - adding tracked courses
  - optional custom course name
  - listing tracked courses with status text
  - stop tracking
  - resume tracking (`Track Again`) for `notified`/`invalid` states
  - automatic tracked-course refresh while signed in
- Course code input is normalized on the client (uppercase alphanumeric, max 6 chars)
- Auto-logout-on-tab-close hook exists but is disabled by default (`AUTO_LOGOUT_ON_TAB_CLOSE=false`)

4. Monitoring worker
- Worker CLI in `src/worker.js`
- Modes:
  - `--init-login`
  - `--init-login --keep-open` (keeps VSB window open until Ctrl+C)
  - `--once`
  - default loop mode
  - `--check-new-course <userId> <cartId>`
- Resume/re-track behavior:
  - resumed/newly-tracked courses are marked for one forced fresh scan before cached JSP reuse
- Compliance/policy controls:
  - minimum poll interval enforcement via `MIN_POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS`
  - emergency monitoring disable via `MONITOR_EMERGENCY_DISABLE`
  - emergency reason support via `MONITOR_EMERGENCY_REASON`
- Monitor flow in `src/monitorService.js` includes:
  - notification dispatch retry/backoff
  - session-failure detection with owner alert path
  - open-seat enqueue flow
  - course state transitions to `notified` after successful delivery/suppressed terminal outcomes
  - invalid-code handling:
    - detects parser “cartid not found” conditions
    - increments invalid attempts
    - after threshold (`INVALID_CODE_MAX_ATTEMPTS`), sends invalid-code email (if notifier supports it) and marks course `invalid`
  - compatibility fallbacks so monitor logic works with both older and newer DB/notifier interfaces

5. VSB source integration and resilience
- Source modes in `src/vsbSource.js`:
  - `browser`
  - `filesystem`
  - `db`
- Browser mode (`src/vsbBrowserSource.js`) supports:
  - shared login session init
  - live `getClassData.jsp` capture
  - tracked-course sync into VSB window
  - presence cache to avoid repeated add loops
  - refresh-window reuse of cached JSP payloads
  - auto re-login attempts (including fallback flows)
  - automatic browser-context reset/relaunch if Playwright context/page closes unexpectedly

6. Notifications
- Notification module exists in `src/notification.js`
- SMTP delivery is implemented via `nodemailer`
- Separate SMTP password override is supported for auth OTP emails (`SMTP_PASS_AUTH`)
- Added invalid-course notification email (`sendInvalidCourseEmail`)
- Course-open and invalid-course emails can include app links via `APP_BASE_URL`
- Delivery attempts are persisted in `notification_attempts`
- Retry/backoff is implemented for transient send failures
- Idempotency + suppression window logic are implemented for course-open alerts

